Notes.Text:
This update for libssh fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2020-1730: Fixed a possible denial of service when using AES-CTR (bsc#1168699).

Vulnerabilities.Description: A flaw was found in libssh versions before 0.8.9 and before 0.9.4 in the way it handled AES-CTR (or DES ciphers if enabled) ciphers. The server or client could crash when the connection hasn't been fully initialized and the system tries to cleanup the ciphers when closing the connection. The biggest threat from this vulnerability is system availability.
